#: ../../../system/qemu-colo.rst:81
msgid "Components"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/qemu-colo.rst:82
msgid ""
"You can see there are several components in COLO's diagram of architecture. "
"Their functions are described below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/qemu-colo.rst:86
msgid "HeartBeat"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/qemu-colo.rst:87
msgid ""
"Runs on both the primary and secondary nodes, to periodically check platform "
"availability. When the primary node suffers a hardware fail-stop failure, "
"the heartbeat stops responding, the secondary node will trigger a failover "
"as soon as it determines the absence."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/qemu-colo.rst:93
msgid "COLO disk Manager"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/qemu-colo.rst:94
msgid ""
"When primary VM writes data into image, the colo disk manager captures this "
"data and sends it to secondary VM's which makes sure the context of "
"secondary VM's image is consistent with the context of primary VM 's image. "
"For more details, please refer to docs/block-replication.txt."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/qemu-colo.rst:100
msgid "Checkpoint/Failover Controller"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/qemu-colo.rst:101
msgid ""
"Modifications of save/restore flow to realize continuous migration, to make "
"sure the state of VM in Secondary side is always consistent with VM in "
"Primary side."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/qemu-colo.rst:106
msgid "COLO Proxy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/qemu-colo.rst:107
msgid ""
"Delivers packets to Primary and Secondary, and then compare the responses "
"from both side. Then decide whether to start a checkpoint according to some "
"rules. Please refer to docs/colo-proxy.txt for more information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/qemu-colo.rst:111
msgid ""
"Note: HeartBeat has not been implemented yet, so you need to trigger "
"failover process by using 'x-colo-lost-heartbeat' command."
msgstr ""

